Claims CLAIMS What is claimed is: 1. A process for removal of nitrates from water, comprising the steps of: a. passing a sample of water through a nano filtration (NF) membrane to obtain a NF permeate and a NF retentate; b. passing the NF permeate obtained in step (a) through a reverse osmosis (RO) membrane to obtain an RO permeate and an RO retentate; c. combining the NF retentate obtained in step (a) with the RO permeate obtained in step (b) so as to produce product water; and d. discarding the RO retentate obtained in step (b); wherein the RO retentate comprises brine having a sodium (Na + ) concentration below about 250 mg/L and a chloride (CI ) concentration below about 450 mg/L. 2. The process according to claim 1, further comprising a step of passing the NF permeate obtained in step (a) through at least one additional NF membrane prior to performing step (b). 3. The process according to claim 2, wherein the NF retentates resulting from each NF step are combined. 4. The process according to claim 3, wherein the combined NF retentates are mixed with the RO permeate. 5. The process according to claim 2, comprising the steps of: a. passing a sample of water through a first NF membrane to obtain a first NF permeate and a first NF retentate; b. passing the first NF permeate obtained in step (a) through a second NF membrane to obtain a second NF permeate and a second NF retentate; c. combining the first and second NF retentates; d. passing the second NF permeate obtained in step (b) through an RO membrane to obtain an RO permeate and an RO retentate; 

 e. combining the combined NF retentate obtained in step (c) with the RO permeate obtained in step (d) so as to produce product water; and f. discarding the RO retentate obtained step (d); wherein the RO retentate comprises brine having a sodium (Na + ) concentration below about 250 mg/L and a chloride (CI ) concentration below about 450 mg/L. 6. The process according to any one of the preceding claims, wherein the NF membrane preferentially rejects Na + , CI " , Ca +2 and/or Mg 2+ ions over N0 3 " ions. 7. The process according to any one of the preceding claims, wherein the NF membrane is selected from the group consisting of DL, DK, NF90, NF245, NF270 and TS80. 8. The process according to any one of the preceding claims, wherein the NF membrane rejects divalent ions selected from Ca +2 and Mg +2 thereby preventing precipitation of said ions in the RO stage. 9. The process according to any one of the preceding claims, wherein the product water in step (c) has a nitrate concentration below about 16.0 mgN/1. 10. The process according to claim 9, wherein the product water in step (c) has a nitrate concentration below about 13.5 mgN/1. 11. The process according to any one of the preceding claims, wherein the brine has a sodium (Na + ) concentration below about 230 mg/L and a chloride (CI ) concentration below about 430 mg/L. 12. A system for removal of nitrates from water, the system comprising: a. at least one nanofiltration (NF) module, each comprising a NF membrane, an inlet for a feed stream, an outlet for a NF permeate stream and an outlet for a NF retentate stream; 

 b. a reverse osmosis (RO) module comprising a RO membrane through which the NF permeate stream passes, an outlet for an RO permeate stream and an outlet for a RO retentate stream; c. a connector connecting the NF retentate stream and the RO permeate stream; wherein the system is adapted to produce product water comprising the NF retentate and RO permeate, and an RO retentate comprising brine having a sodium (Na + ) concentration below about 250 mg/L and a chloride (CI ) concentration below about 450 mg/L. 13. The system according to claim 12, which is adapted to produce an RO retentate comprising brine having a sodium (Na + ) concentration below about 230 mg/L and a chloride (CI ) concentration below about 430 mg/L.
